Package: BSS
Type: Package
Title: BSS
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2026-20-06
Author: Rafael Lambertucci
Maintainer: Rafael Lambertucci <rlambertucci@unifesp.br>
Description: This module provides a variety of statistical procedures for different data analysis needs. The main features include: 
  1) Network analysis for continuous and mixed data; 
  2) Missing value analysis and data imputation using the missRanger and MICE;
  3) Outlier detection using Dixons' Q Test, boxplots and the modified z-score with adjustable thresholds, including options for outlier treatment;
  4) Post hoc analysis for MANOVA using descriptive discriminant analysis (including effect size calculation); 
  5) Comprehensive pairwise effect size calculation for independent and longitudinal designs; 
  6) Sample size calculation for finite populations (using two different formulas) and for animal experimental designs based on the Resource Equation Approach; 
  7) Statistical comparison of correlation coefficients (independent and dependent);
  8) Highly customizable group comparison plots (bar charts, boxplots, and mean-dispersion graphs) for both cross-sectional and longitudinal designs, including automated publication-ready descriptive tables (APA, ABNT, Vancouver, and Chicago styles).
